---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config";

// TODO: have this reviewed (and the effective date confirmed) before launch.
// This is a working draft, not legal advice.
const effectiveDate = "June 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — HermeΣ"
  description="How HermeΣ collects, uses, and protects your chapter's information."
>
  <section class="px-6 pt-20 pb-24 md:px-12">
    <div class="prose-hermes mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-gold mb-4 text-xs font-medium tracking-[5px] uppercase">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="font-display mb-2 text-[clamp(40px,6vw,64px)] leading-none tracking-[3px] text-white">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-cream-dim mb-10 text-sm">Effective: {effectiveDate}</p>

      <p>
        This policy explains what information {SITE.legalEntity} ("HermeΣ," "we," "us") collects,
        how we use it, and the choices you have. We built HermeΣ for chapters, and we treat your
        chapter's information the way we'd want ours treated.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-cream">Contact information you give us</strong> — name, email,
          chapter/organization, role, and message contents when you submit a form or book a demo.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-cream">Chapter content we process on your behalf</strong> — when your
          chapter uses HermeΣ, we process the meeting-minutes documents posted to your designated
          Slack channel in order to generate summaries, action items, and calendar events. We only
          read the channel you designate.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-cream">Basic technical data</strong> — standard server logs collected
          by our hosting provider (such as IP address and pages visited) used for security and
          site operation.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to demo requests and provide the service your chapter signs up for.</li>
        <li>To generate your chapter's summaries, task lists, and calendar updates.</li>
        <li>To operate, secure, and improve the service.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell your information. We do not use your chapter's meeting content for anything
        other than serving your chapter.
      </p>

      <h2>Service providers</h2>
      <p>
        HermeΣ runs on third-party platforms that process data as part of delivering the service:
        Slack (message and file access in your designated channel), Google (calendar events),
        AI-processing providers (document understanding for summaries), Netlify (website hosting
        and form submissions), and Calendly (demo scheduling). Each processes only what is needed
        for its role.
      </p>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep form submissions as long as needed to handle your request and our business records.
        Chapter meeting content is processed to generate outputs and retained only as needed to
        operate the service. You may request deletion at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You can request access to, correction of, or deletion of your information by emailing
        <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>. If your chapter stops
        using HermeΣ, we'll delete chapter content on request.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If we make material changes to this policy, we'll update this page and the effective date
        above.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
